Budget Director James Miller saidPresident Reagan would veto the Democrat-controlled Congress'new budget -- but offered to compromise on raising revenues.    "If that budget comes down it will be vetoed out of hand, Ican tell you that," Miller said on NBC's "Today" program.    He said Reagan would not accept the 19 billion dlr taxincrease in Congress' proposal but said "keep in mind thepresident has proposed certain revenues in his budget.    "They're not taxes," Miller said. "They are user charges andasset sales. I think there is some room there we can sit downand talk with the Democrats about." Reuter&#3;